Idiomlexika thematisiert.  aThe present collected volume contains eleven papers by internationally renowned phraseologists and dictionary compilers giving an overview of the present state of the art in research into lexicographical phraseology from an intra-lingual and interlingual perspective. Selected individual examples are presented to document positive recent developments in the compilation of idiomatic dictionaries, with particular acknowledgement of the achievements of computational linguistics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGerman languagexIdioms. 0aGerman languagexLexicography. 0aGerman languagexPhraseology. 0aIdioms. 0aLexicography. 0aPhraseology. 4aLexikographie. 4aPhraseologie. 4aSprachwissenschaft. 4aWörterbuch. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / German.2bisacsh  aDictionary.  aLexicography.  aLinguistics.  aPhraseology.1 aBurger, Harald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDobrovol\x27skij, Dmitrij, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEttinger, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFilipenko, Tat’jana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGlenk, Eva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHallsteinsdóttir, Erla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeine, Antje, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJesenšek, Vida, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMellado Blanco, Carmen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMellado-Blanco, Carmen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPiirainen, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchemann, Hans